ADDITIONAL ENQUIRIES 

34 Fairfield Road, Uxbridge , UB8 1AL



General



Please provide a certified copy Grant of Probate. 



Please provide us with your bank details in order that we may verify the same ahead of completion.



Please provide us with your undertaking to adopt the Law Society's Code for Completion by Post 2019. This can be given in replies to standard requisitions on title (3rd edition) or separately but must be received prior to exchange of contracts. 



Legal Title



Please confirm whether any problems have been experienced with regards to any of the rights granted or those reserved.



Please confirm that there have been no breaches of any of the covenants contained or referred to in the Charges Register, 2004 Lease and 1975 Lease.



2004 Lease and 1975 Lease



We note our client is to become a member of the management company on completion. Please confirm the original shares certificate and 2STF's will be provided on completion. 



We note we are to provide the landlord with notice on completion. Please contact the Landlord with regards to their requirements and fees as mentioned within the completed form LPE1 by the managing agent. 



We note our client is to enter into a Deed of Covenant on completion.  Please contact the Landlord in relation to their fees and requirements as suggested within the completed form LPE1 by the managing agent. Please also provide us with a draft Deed of Covenant as approved by the Landlord. 



Please provide a complete copy of the 1975 Lease.  If the same cannot be provided please provide a draft indemnity insurance policy for approval. 



Protocol Forms



With regards to the Leasehold Information Form:-

We note the seller's response to 1.2 however the 1975 Lease outlines ground rent of £60.00 per annum is payable. Please clarify. 

Please ask the seller to complete section 2, section 4, number 5.4 and 10.2.



With regards to the Property Information Form:-

Please provide Fensa for the replacement windows mentioned at 4.1(c).

Please ask the seller to complete 5.1(d), 5.1(g), 5.1(h), 5.1(i) and 7.5.

We note your client's response at 6.1 however please clarify the position. Does the management company not obtain insurance for the whole block. 

We note the seller's response at 14.3 however the legal title outline there is a charge currently against the property.  Please clarify. 



We note the Property Information Form and Fittings and Contents Form were completed back in August 2020.  Please confirm that the information contained therein remains accurate and up to date.  From the date of the forms, please confirm whether a previous sale has fallen through and if so, please advise of the reason.



Searches



Please provide the following planning permissions revealed within our Local Authority search:-

Planning 6177/TRE/2017/112 approved 31 July 2017.

Planning 6177/TRE/2011/6 split decision (p) 5 April 2011.

Planning 6177/TRE/2003/136 split decision (p) 15 December 2003.

Planning 6177/TRE/2001/165 approved 21 January 2002.



Management Pack



Please provide an up to date statement of accounts to include the service charge demand for 1 January 2021 to 30 June 2021.



Please confirm all service charge and ground rent will be paid in full on completion. We note the last demand is not paid in full. 



Please confirm that the following condition may be added to the contract – “On completion, the Buyers solicitors shall retain the sum of £500 on account of service charge due for the period of the Seller’s ownership of the property to completion. If a negative amount is established once accounts have been finalised, that sum of up to £500 shall be paid to the Buyer within 14 days of evidence being provided to the Sellers solicitors. If a positive amount is established, the retention shall be released to the Sellers Solicitors. If the liability has not been ascertained within 12 months of completion, the retained sum shall be released to the Sellers solicitors absolutely.”



Please provide the management pack from Freeholder Royle Estates (hoddesdon) Limited who currently deals with the ground rent payable. 



Cladding:-

Has any cladding (including but not limited to Aluminium Composite Material (ACM), Metal Composite Materials (MCM) (faced with metals such as zinc, copper and stainless steel) or High Pressure Laminates (HPL) cladding) been used in the original construction (or subsequent refurbishment as may be applicable) of any part of the external envelope of the buildings at the Property?

Are any of the buildings at the Property greater than 3 storeys and/or 18m in height?

Has the building owner/manager had the external envelope of any buildings at the Property assessed and obtained a written EWS1 report confirming compliance with the functional requirements of current Building Regulations and Fire Regulations, and any guidance provided by the MHCLG? If so, please provide a copy of the completed EWS1 report.  If not, why not





Foot Anstey LLP
